# Git Worktrees for Parallel Work

Multiple agents working on this repo **must use git worktrees** so each branch lives in its own directory. This prevents agents from accidentally editing files on the wrong branch and avoids the "nothing to commit" confusion that occurs when an agent switches branches mid-session.

## Setup a new worktree

```bash
# Add a worktree for a new feature branch
git worktree add ../coach-board-feat-my-feature -b feat/my-feature origin/staging/kc-current

# Work inside that directory
cd ../coach-board-feat-my-feature
```

## List / remove worktrees

```bash
git worktree list
git worktree remove ../coach-board-feat-my-feature
```

## Rules

- **Never `git checkout` to switch branches** in the main worktree while another agent is active — create a worktree instead.
- Name worktrees `../coach-board-<branch-slug>` (sibling of the main repo dir) to keep them easy to find.
- Worktrees share the same `.git` directory, so all branches/remotes are visible everywhere.
- Remove the worktree after the PR is merged: `git worktree remove <path>`.
- The **main worktree** (`/Users/mcaron/Sites/coach-board`) should stay on `staging/kc-current`.
